Class UploaderTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.concurrent.FutureTask<V>
      • javafx.concurrent.Task<UploaderTaskResult>
        • main.UploaderTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, java.util.concurrent.Future<UploaderTaskResult>, java.util.concurrent.RunnableFuture<UploaderTaskResult>, javafx.concurrent.Worker<UploaderTaskResult>, javafx.event.EventTarget

    public class UploaderTask
extends javafx.concurrent.Task<UploaderTaskResult>
    An extension of JavaFX's Task to be run in a new thread separate from the JavaFX Application Thread. Upon call, creates an FTP client instance, configures connection to the server, and uploads the file(s) to the server. Returns an UploaderTaskResult that contains the message and alert type for the AutoUploadFiles, whether successful or failed.

    • Property Detail

      • string

        public final javafx.beans.property.StringProperty stringProperty
        Returns the StringProperty contained in this uploader task. This is a manually implemented StringProperty and is not one of the Property values automatically created for a standard Task, such as progress, title, or message. May be removed in the future and replaced with message, which will need its updateMessage(String) overridden to run under Platform.runLater(). When previously used, message did not update with the console properly.
        See Also:
        getString(), setString(String)
